P(Z ≥ 0.5) = 1 - P(Z < 0.5) = 1 - Φ(0.5)

From standard normal tables: Φ(0.5) ≈ 0.6915

Therefore: P(Z ≥ 0.5) = 1 - 0.6915 = 0.3085

