- P(A ∪ B') = 0.87

I'll use the fact that B and B' partition the sample space, so B ∪ B' = S (the entire sample space).

For any set A:
A = A ∩ S = A ∩ (B ∪ B') = (A ∩ B) ∪ (A ∩ B')

Since (A ∩ B) and (A ∩ B') are disjoint:
P(A) = P(A ∩ B) + P(A ∩ B')

Now I'll express the given conditions in terms of these probabilities.

From P(A ∪ B) = 0.76:
P(A ∪ B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A ∩ B) = 0.76

From P(A ∪ B') = 0.87:
