Since P(B) + P(B') = 1, we have P(B') = 1 - P(B).

Adding the two equations:
P(A) + P(B) - P(A ∩ B) + P(A) + P(B') - P(A ∩ B') = 0.76 + 0.87

2P(A) + P(B) + P(B') - P(A ∩ B) - P(A ∩ B') = 1.63

2P(A) + 1 - [P(A ∩ B) + P(A ∩ B')] = 1.63

Since P(A ∩ B) + P(A ∩ B') = P(A):
2P(A) + 1 - P(A) = 1.63

P(A) + 1 = 1.63

P(A) = 0.63

Let me verify this:
