1 ≥ 3x
x ≤ 1/3

So for x ∈ [0, 1/2], the condition is satisfied when x ∈ [0, 1/3].

By symmetry, if x > 1/2 (so 1 - x is the shorter part), the condition is:
x/(1 - x) ≥ 2
x ≥ 2(1 - x)
x ≥ 2 - 2x
3x ≥ 2
x ≥ 2/3

So for x ∈ [1/2, 1], the condition is satisfied when x ∈ [2/3, 1].

The total favorable region is:
- [0, 1/3]: length = 1/3
- [2/3, 1]: length = 1/3
- Total favorable length = 1/3 + 1/3 = 2/3

The probability is:
P = (2/3) / 1 = 2/3 ≈ 0.667

