Y₇ < 27.3 means that the 7th order statistic is less than 27.3.

This is equivalent to saying: at least 7 out of 8 observations are less than 27.3.

Let me think about this differently. Y₇ < 27.3 means that at most 1 observation is greater than or equal to 27.3.

For each observation, the probability of being less than 27.3 is p = 0.70.
The probability of being greater than or equal to 27.3 is 1 - p = 0.30.

Y₇ < 27.3 occurs when at least 7 observations fall below 27.3, which means at most 1 observation is at or above 27.3.

This is a binomial probability:
P(Y₇ < 27.3) = P(at most 1 observation ≥ 27.3)
